{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1857","published":"2024-07-19T11:08:32Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:23.405699Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-38517"],"summary":"rapidjson security update","details":"RapidJSON as a fast JSON parser which generator for c++. It`s inspired by RapidXML. It`s supports both SAX &amp; DOM style API. It`s small but complete. It`s fast, It`s preformance can be comparabel to strlen(). It`s self-contained. It doesn`t depend on external libraries such as BOOST. It`s Unicode and memory friendly, each JSON valude occupies exactly 16/20 bytes for most 32/64-bit machines. It`s suport UTF-8 UTF-16 UTF-32 (LE &amp; BE).\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nTencent RapidJSON is vulnerable to privilege escalation due to an integer underflow in the `GenericReader::ParseNumber()` function of `include/rapidjson/reader.h` when parsing JSON text from a stream. An attacker needs to send the victim a crafted file which needs to be opened; this triggers the integer underflow vulnerability (when the file is parsed), leading to elevation of privilege.(CVE-2024-38517)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"rapidjson","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/rapidjson&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.1.0-13.oe2403"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"noarch":["rapidjson-devel-1.1.0-13.oe2403.noarch.rpm","rapidjson-help-1.1.0-13.oe2403.noarch.rpm"],"src":["rapidjson-1.1.0-13.oe2403.src.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2024-1857.json"}},{"package":{"name":"rapidjson","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP4","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/rapidjson&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.1.0-12.oe2203sp4"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"noarch":["rapidjson-devel-1.1.0-12.oe2203sp4.noarch.rpm","rapidjson-help-1.1.0-12.oe2203sp4.noarch.rpm"],"src":["rapidjson-1.1.0-12.oe2203sp4.src.rpm"]},"database_specif